{"title_page": "Trumpets (Jason Derulo song)", "text_new": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = Trumpets\n| cover      = Trumpets - Single Cover.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Jason Derulo]]\n| album      = [[Tattoos (album)|Tattoos]] {{noitalic|and}} [[Talk Dirty (album)|Talk Dirty]]\n| released   =\n* November 7, 2013 (UK)\n* August 19, 2014 (US)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/1xtra/playlist/ |title=BBC \u2013 Radio 1Xtra \u2013 Playlist |publisher=Archive.is |accessdate=2014-02-22 |url-status=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20131109082311/http://www.bbc.co.uk/1xtra/playlist/ |archivedate=2013-11-09 }}</ref>\n| format     =\n* [[Music download|Digital download]]\n* [[CD single]]\n| recorded   = 2012\n| studio     =\n* [[Atlantic Studios]]\n* ([[Hollywood]], [[California]])\n| venue      =\n| genre      =\n* [[Pop music|Pop]]\n* [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]\n| length     = 3:37\n| label      = [[Warner Bros. Records|Warner Bros.]]\n| writer     =\n* [[Jason Derulo|Jason Desrouleaux]]\n* [[Jon Bellion]]\n| producer   = [[Jon Bellion]]\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n| misc       = {{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[Jason Derulo]]\n | type       = single\n | prev_title = [[Marry Me (Jason Derulo song)|Marry Me]]\n | prev_year  = 2013\n | title      = Trumpets\n | year       = 2013\n | next_title = [[Stupid Love (Jason Derulo song)|Stupid Love]]\n | next_year  = 2014\n}}\n}}\n\n\"'''Trumpets'''\" is a song by American singer [[Jason Derulo]], released as the fourth single in Australia,  New Zealand and the European  market and third single in the UK, from his third studio album, ''[[Tattoos (album)|Tattoos]]'' (2013). The song was written by Derulo (under his real name Jason Desrouleaux) and [[Jon Bellion]], who also handled the production.\n\nAlthough the song wasn't released as a single in the United States at the time, it was included on the US version of the album, ''[[Talk Dirty (album)|Talk Dirty]]'' (2014). \"Trumpets\" was released in the US as the fifth single from ''Talk Dirty''<ref>http://www.singersroom.com/content/2014-07-10/Jason-Derulo-Ready-For-Fifth-Album-Confirms-Next-Single/</ref> and has since peaked at number 14 on the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]]. It was sent to US pop and rhythmic radio on August 19, 2014.<ref>http://www.allaccess.com/top40-rhythmic/future-releases</ref>\n\n==Background==\nFollowing the release of \"[[Marry Me (Jason Derulo song)|Marry Me]]\" as the third single from his album ''[[Tattoos]]'' in the US and some international markets, \"Trumpets\" was released as the fourth overall single from the album to the UK and European territories. \"Trumpets\" was written by [[Jason Derulo|Jason Desrouleaux]] and [[Jon Bellion]] who also handled the production.<ref name=\"album credits\">{{cite AV media notes |title=Tattoos|titlelink=Tattoos (album)|others=[[Jason Derulo]] |year=2013 |type=Booklet |publisher=[[Beluga Heights Records|Beluga Heights]], [[Warner Bros. Records|Warner Bros]]}}</ref> The song was recorded by Vince Watson at Atlantic Studios in Hollywood, California.<ref name=\"album credits\" /> with additional recordings by Josh Collins and Juan P. Negrete.<ref name=\"album credits\" /> It was mixed by Roberto \"Tito\" Vazquez at Plush recording Studios in Orlando Florida.<ref name=\"album credits\" /> It was mastered by Tom Coyne at sterling Sound in New York.<ref name=\"album credits\" />\n\n==Composition==\n\"Trumpets\" is a midtempo [[Pop music|pop]] and [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]] song written in the key of [[C major]],<ref>http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/6553115/the-two-sides-of-jason-derulo</ref> that runs for a duration of three minutes and thirty seven seconds and was written by [[Jason Derulo]] and [[Jon Bellion]], who also handled the song's production.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kempiredaily.com/new-music-jason-derulo-trumpets-lyric-video |title=<nowiki>New Music: Jason Derulo \u2013 \u201cTrumpets\u201d [Lyric Video</nowiki> |publisher=Kempire Daily |date= |accessdate=2014-02-22}}</ref> Lyrically the song is about being so in love with and infatuated with someone that every time you're together, trumpets blast through your head, as heard in the lyrics \"Every time that you get undressed/ I hear symphonies in my head.\"<ref name=\"buzzworthy.mtv.com\">{{cite web|author=Jenna Hally Rubenstein |url=http://buzzworthy.mtv.com/2013/11/05/jason-derulo-trumpets-video/ |title=Jason Derulo Hears Actual 'Trumpets,' Oddly, Feels Like Katy Perry Every Time He's About To Get Some In His New Video |publisher=Buzzworthy.mtv.com |date=2013-11-05 |accessdate=2014-02-22}}</ref> It also states how various features of Jason's girlfriend remind him of other songs by other artists, including [[Coldplay]] (her eyes\u2014 possibly a reference to \"[[A Rush of Blood to the Head|Green Eyes]]\"), [[Katy Perry]] (her bra\u2014 possibly a reference to \"[[California Gurls]]\", in the video for which Perry dons a distinctive cream-shooting bra) and [[Kanye West]] (her rear\u2014 possibly a reference to the [[2 Chainz]] and [[Kanye West]] single \"[[Birthday Song]]\", which features many lyrics about \"booty\").\n\n==Music video==\nOn October 11, 2013, the official lyric video for the song premiered on Derulo's official YouTube channel, after which he tweeted '#trumpets #tattoos' with a link to the video, to help promote the song's release.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://singersroom.com/content/2013-10-13/Jason-Derulo-Trumpets-Lyric-Video/ |title=Videos &#124; Jason Derulo \u2013 Trumpets (Lyric Video) |publisher=Singersroom |date=2013-10-13 |accessdate=2014-02-22}}</ref> The music video for \"Trumpets\" made its world premiere online through Derulo's official [[YouTube]] channel on November 3, 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.directlyrics.com/jason-derulo-trumpets-news.html |title=Jason Derulo \u2013 \"Trumpets\" Music Videos |publisher=Directlyrics.com |date=2013-11-04 |accessdate=2014-02-22}}</ref> The video depicts Jason attempting to have sex with a young woman. Just as she takes off her clothes, he is bombarded by the sound of instruments and a marching band bursts into his bedroom.<ref name=\"buzzworthy.mtv.com\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rap-up.com/2013/11/04/video-jason-derulo-trumpets/ |title=Video: Jason Derulo \u2013 'Trumpets' |publisher=Rap-Up.com |date= |accessdate=2014-02-22}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=5th November 2013, 09:50 |url=http://www.capitalfm.com/artists/jason-derulo/videos/trumpets/ |title=Jason Derulo \u2013 'Trumpets' (Official Video): Music Video |publisher=Capital FM |date=2013-11-05 |accessdate=2014-02-22}}</ref>\nThe music video was directed by Jason Derulo as his directorial debut alongside Colin Tilley who has directed many of Derulo's previous videos and was produced by Jamee Ranta.<ref name=\"dailystar.co.uk\">{{cite web|last=Carr |first=Kim |url=http://www.dailystar.co.uk/showbiz/playlist/356421/Jason-Derulo-is-on-a-roll |title=Jason Derulo is on a roll &#124; Playlist &#124; Showbiz & TV &#124; Daily Star. Simply The Best 7 Days A Week |publisher=Dailystar.co.uk |date=2013-12-18 |accessdate=2014-02-22}}</ref> Derulo got backlash for the video from his record label for directing the video saying \"it wasn't the right move or look, because I directed it.\" states Derulo.<ref name=\"dailystar.co.uk\" /> He worked on it with Collin Tilley and got pictures in the background, singing the lyrics along with him.<ref name=\"dailystar.co.uk\" />\n\n==Live performances==\nDerulo performed \"Trumpets\" live for the first time in the UK on BBC Radio 1 1Xtra special performance in the Live Lounge.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p01n4vql |title=BBC Radio 1 \u2013 Fearne Cotton, Jason Derulo in the Live Lounge, Jason Derulo \u2013 Trumpets in the Live Lounge |publisher=Bbc.co.uk |date=2013-12-10 |accessdate=2014-02-22}}</ref> He also performed the song at the [[Capital (radio network)|Capital FM]] [[Jingle Ball|Jingle Bell Ball]] on December 8, 2013, along with his debut single \"[[Whatcha Say]]\", \"The Other Side\", \"In My Head\" and \"Talk Dirty\".<ref>{{cite web|author=8th December 2013, 21:01 |url=http://www.capitalfm.com/artists/jason-derulo/performances/trumpets-live-jingle-bell-ball-2013/ |title=Jason Derulo - 'Trumpets' (Live Performance, Jingle Bell Ball 2013): pictures, news, songs, tours |publisher=Capital FM |date=2013-12-08 |accessdate=2014-02-22}}</ref> Derulo made his first televised performance of the song during a promotional tour in the UK on ''[[The Paul O'Grady Show]]'' on December 10, 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jasonderulo.com/news/jason-derulo-performs-trumpets-live-uk-paul-o-grady-show-208651 |title=Jason Derulo Performs \"Trumpets\" Live in the UK on the Paul O'Grady Show! \u2013 Jason Derulo Latest News |publisher=Jasonderulo.com |date=2013-12-13 |accessdate=2014-02-22}}</ref> Derulo also performed this track on New Years Day for the Dick Clark post show. On July 4, 2014, Derulo performed it on ''[[Good Morning America]]'' as part of its Summer Concert Series.<ref>{{cite web|title=Jason Derulo Rocks NYC With 'Trumpets,' 'The Other Side'|url=http://abcnews.go.com/GMA/video/jason-derulo-rocks-central-park-trumpets-24426990|website=ABC News|accessdate=August 16, 2014|date=July 4, 2014}}</ref> He performed the song during the ''[[MDA Show of Strength]]'' that aired on August 31, 2014, but was taped in May 2014.\n\n==Release and artwork==\nThe artwork for the single features several of the same trumpet seen in Derulo's CGI neck tattoo on the album cover of ''[[Tattoos (album)|Tattoos]]''. On November 7, the single was first released in the UK. It was added to the playlist of British [[urban contemporary]] station [[BBC Radio 1Xtra]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/1xtra/playlist/ |title=Radio 1Xtra Playlist \u2013 Thursday 7th November |work=[[BBC Radio 1Xtra]] |publisher=BBC |accessdate=November 8, 2013 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20131109082311/http://www.bbc.co.uk/1xtra/playlist/ |archivedate=November 9, 2013}}</ref> It has since been released to many international territories while \"[[Talk Dirty (Jason Derulo song)|Talk Dirty]]\" was released in the US as the third single.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QXjt0WdgTF4 |title=Jason Derulo 'Talks Dirty' & Jordin Sparks' NSYNC Love! (JINGLE BALL 2013) |publisher=YouTube |date=2013-12-16 |accessdate=2014-02-22}}</ref>\n\n==Chart performance==\n\"Trumpets\" first appeared on the [[Dutch Top 40]] in the Netherlands issue dated November 30, 2013, debuting at its current peak position of number 22.<ref>{{cite web|author=Stichting Nederlandse Top 40 |url=http://www.top40.nl/top40/2013/week-48 |title=Top 40-lijst van week 48, 2013 |publisher=Top40.nl |date= |accessdate=2014-02-22}}</ref> In Australia, \"Trumpets\" debuted at number 22 the [[ARIA Charts|ARIA Singles Chart]] issue dated December 15, 2013: it reached its peak position of number one in its fourth week on the chart.<ref>{{cite web|author=Steffen Hung |url=http://australian-charts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Jason+Derulo&titel=Trumpets&cat=s |title=Jason Derulo \u2013 Trumpets |publisher=australian-charts.com |date= |accessdate=2014-02-22}}</ref> It has also made an appearance on the [[Recorded Music NZ|New Zealand Top 40 Singles Chart]], where it debuted at number 31, and has since reached its current peak of number 3.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nztop40.co.nz/chart/singles?chart=2341 |title=NZ Top 40 Singles Chart &#124; The Official New Zealand Music Chart |publisher=Nztop40.co.nz |date=2013-12-16 |accessdate=2014-02-22}}</ref>\n\n\"Trumpets\" made its debut on the UK R&B Singles Chart at number fifteen,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/archive-chart/_/16/2013-11-23/ |title=2013-11-23 Top 40 R&B Singles Archive |publisher=Official Charts |date=2013-11-23 |accessdate=2014-02-22}}</ref> it has since reached its peak position of number one in its fifth week on the chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/archive-chart/_/16/2013-12-21/ |title=2013-12-21 Top 40 R&B Singles Archive |publisher=Official Charts |date=2013-12-21 |accessdate=2014-02-22}}</ref> It reached number 4 on the UK Singles Chart, becoming his third Top 10 single from the album and his eighth overall.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/archive-chart/_/1/2013-12-21/ |title=2013-12-21 Top 40 Official Singles Chart UK Archive |publisher=Official Charts |date=2013-12-21 |accessdate=2014-02-22}}</ref> \"Trumpets\" remained at fourth position for four consecutive weeks.\n\nThe song reached a peak of No. 14 on the Billboard Hot 100, and has sold over a million copies in the US as of October 2014.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://music.yahoo.com/blogs/chart-watch/chart-watch-fergie-shows-l-a-some-love-171456124.html |title=Chart Watch: Fergie Shows L.A. Some Love |author= Paul Grein |date=October 23, 2014 |work=Yahoo! Music (Chart Watch) }}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n* '''Digital download'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/au/album/trumpets/id684559674 |title=iTunes \u2013 Music \u2013 Tattoos by Jason Derulo |publisher=Itunes.apple.com |date=2013-09-20 |accessdate=2014-02-22}}</ref>\n# \"Trumpets\" \u2013 3:37\n\n==Charts==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Chart (2013\u201314)\n! Peak<br/>position\n|-\n{{singlechart|Australia|1|artist=Jason Derulo|song=Trumpets}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | Australia Urban ([[ARIA Charts|ARIA]])<ref name=\"ARIA Urban\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ariacharts.com.au/chart/urban-singles |title=Top 40 Urban Singles Chart \u2013 30/12/2013 |publisher=[[Australian Recording Industry Association]] (ARIA)}}</ref> \n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|1\n|-\n{{singlechart|Austria|33|artist=Jason Derulo|song=Trumpets}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Flanders|10|artist=Jason Derulo|song=Trumpets|accessdate=January 1